sec.p:
Coverage indicates the fraction of ProteinConformers-lite’s low-energy regions recovered by the generative model:
(2)
Coverage=|A∩B||A| \begin{document}$$\displaystyle \begin{equation*} \text { Coverage }=\frac{|A \cap B|}{|A|} \tag{2} \end{equation*}$$\end{document}

Jaccard Index provides a symmetric measure of shared low-energy regions:
(3)
Jaccard Index=|A∩B||A|+|B|−|A∩B| \begin{document}$$\displaystyle \begin{equation*} \text { Jaccard Index }=\frac{|A \cap B|}{|A|+|B|-|A \cap B|} \tag{3} \end{equation*}$$\end{document}

CGMSmah incorporates both directional and magnitude alignment through a composite Mahalanobis distance and a Gaussian radial basis function, imposing a stronger penalty on local discrepancies. The Mahalanobis distance is defined as:
(5)
dM(ui,uj)=(ui−uj)TΣ−1(ui−uj) \begin{document}$$\displaystyle \begin{equation*} \mathrm{d}_{M}\left(u_{i}, u_{j}\right)=\sqrt{\left(u_{i}-u_{j}\right)^{T} \Sigma^{-1}\left(u_{i}-u_{j}\right)} \tag{5} \end{equation*}$$\end{document}
where Σ in (5) is the covariance matrix between two vectors. This distance is then transformed via a Gaussian kernel to compute the similarity:
(6)
CGMSmah=1|C|∑(i,j)∈Cexp⁡(−12(dM(ui,uj)2) \begin{document}$$\displaystyle \begin{equation*} \mathrm{CGMS}^{\mathrm{mah}}=\frac{1}{|C|} \sum_{(i, j) \in C} \exp \left(-\frac{1}{2}\left(d_{M}\left(u_{i}, u_{j}\right)^{2}\right)\right. \tag{6} \end{equation*}$$\end{document}
